Johannesburg – So, what exactly does 2021 have in store for our hair? We decided to go to the source and ask some professional hairstylists for their expert insight. Darling Hair has been the official Hair styling partner for season 16 of South Africa’s biggest competition reality show, Idols SA. They set the tone for the 10 of the biggest hair trends for the year ahead. Use Darling Hair’s “Do you Braid” Trending technique of braids with seamless blending of natural hair with the extensions   Use Darling Hair’s “ Passion Twist” Natural looking twist with a bit of a messy effect for that unique look   Use Darling Hair’s “Crochet Goddess Locs” Natural looking locs with wavey ends. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21626" src="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nomzamo-Mbatha.jpg" alt="" width="299" height="357" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nomzamo-Mbatha.jpg 299w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nomzamo-Mbatha-251x300.jpg 251w" sizes="(max-width: 299px) 100vw, 299px" /> Use Darling Hair’s “Straight Pony” Softly twisting a ponytail giving it an edgy but elegant look   Use Darling Hair’s “Afro Bulk” Versatile classic afro look with a number of ways to wear it <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21621" src="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Classic-afro.png" alt="" width="299" height="492" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Classic-afro.png 299w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Classic-afro-182x300.png 182w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Classic-afro-255x420.png 255w" sizes="(max-width: 299px) 100vw, 299px" /> Use Darling Hair’s “Marley Kinky” Natural style given a layered look for fullness and edginess <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21628" src="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Soft-Twisted.png" alt="" width="296" height="306" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Soft-Twisted.png 296w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Soft-Twisted-290x300.png 290w" sizes="(max-width: 296px) 100vw, 296px" /> Use Darling Hair’s “Beach Wave” Curls combed out a bit texture for a romantic soft look   Use Darling Hair’s – Empress Brazilian Classic that is constantly re – invented to keep up with the trends   Use Darling Hair’s “Classic Kinky” Two tone curls with a little styling to give them a fresh look <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21627" src="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Soft-sift-curls.png" alt="" width="288" height="398" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Soft-sift-curls.png 288w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Soft-sift-curls-217x300.png 217w" sizes="(max-width: 288px) 100vw, 288px" />  Use Darling Hair’s “Jozi Short Dred” Dreadlocks given a fresh edgy twist <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21620" src="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bob-dred.png" alt="" width="283" height="383" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bob-dred.png 283w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Bob-dred-222x300.png 222w" sizes="(max-width: 283px) 100vw, 283px" />  Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. 